VERSION     = "1.5.0"
DESCRIPTION = "Cable AI Scalp v1.5 — added H1 over-extension band filter. signals.py measures how far the entry sits beyond the H1 EMA in the trade's own direction (BUY: price-EMA, SELL: EMA-price), stores levels['h1_ext_pips']/['h1_ext_in_band'], and shadow-logs an 'H1 ext | ...' line every cycle. Enforcement lives in bot.py's filter stack (after the news re-derivation of position_usd, before units are sized): mode 'off' = shadow only, 'soft' = trade still fires at position_usd * h1_ext_soft_haircut (default 0.5), 'strict' = hard block. Backtest (Jun-Jul 2026, GBP/USD) showed the 5-20p band held the only net-positive trades while entries <=5p (just-flipped whipsaw) or >=20p (extended chase) lost. Ships in 'off' to confirm the band out-of-sample before it gates or resizes live orders."
